### Initialize and Configure Lexical Editor (Vanilla JS)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/getting-started/quick-start

This snippet shows how to initialize and configure a Lexical editor in a Vanilla JavaScript environment. It involves getting DOM element references, defining initial editor configuration (namespace, nodes, theme), and setting up the root element. Dependencies include Lexical core and specific node types like HeadingNode and QuoteNode.

```javascript
const editorRef = document.getElementById('lexical-editor');
const stateRef = document.getElementById('lexical-state') as HTMLTextAreaElement;

const initialConfig = {
  namespace: 'Vanilla JS Demo',
  // Register nodes specific for @lexical/rich-text
  nodes: [HeadingNode, QuoteNode],
  onError: (error: Error) => {
    throw error;
  },
  theme: {
    // Adding styling to Quote node, see styles.css
    quote: 'PlaygroundEditorTheme__quote',
  },
};

const editor = createEditor(initialConfig);
editor.setRootElement(editorRef);
```

