### Lexical Update Listener with React

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/getting-started/react

This React component registers an update listener with the Lexical editor. It uses `useEffect` to ensure proper cleanup and listens for changes in the editor state, calling an `onChange` prop with the latest editor state.

```jsx
function MyOnChangePlugin({ onChange }) {
  // Access the editor through the LexicalComposerContext
  const [editor] = useLexicalComposerContext();
  // Wrap our listener in useEffect to handle the teardown and avoid stale references.
  useEffect(() => {
    // most listeners return a teardown function that can be called to clean them up.
    return editor.registerUpdateListener(({editorState}) => {
      // call onChange here to pass the latest state up to the parent.
      onChange(editorState);
    });
  }, [editor, onChange]);
  return null;
}
