### Get List Node Depth

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_list

Utility function to determine the nesting depth of a given ListNode within the Lexical editor's root. It recursively checks the parent nodes.

```typescript
function $getListDepth(listNode: ListNode): number {
  // Implementation details...
  let depth = 0;
  let currentNode = listNode;
  while (currentNode.getParent() !== null && !currentNode.isRoot()) {
    depth++;
    currentNode = currentNode.getParent() as ListNode; // Assuming parent is also a ListNode or similar structure
  }
  return depth;
}
```

