### Incorrect LexicalExtensionComposer Usage with Unstable Extension (React)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_react_LexicalExtensionComposer

This example illustrates an incorrect way to use LexicalExtensionComposer, where the extension is defined directly within the component body without memoization. This leads to the editor being re-created on every render, causing loss of all editor state.

```javascript
import { LexicalExtensionComposer } from '@lexical/react/LexicalExtensionComposer';
import { defineExtension } from '@lexical/react/LexicalUtils';
import { RichTextExtension } from '@lexical/rich-text';
import { HistoryExtension } from '@lexical/history';
import { EmojiExtension } from '@lexical/emoji';

function MyBrokenEditor({ emojiBaseUrl, children }) {
  // This argument is not stable, the editor is re-created every render and
  // all state is lost!
  const extension = defineExtension({
    name: "[root]",
    dependencies: [RichTextExtension, HistoryExtension, EmojiExtension]
  });

  return (<LexicalExtensionComposer extension={extension}>{children}</LexicalExtensionComposer>);
}
```

