### Create State with Parse, isEqual, and Unparse (TypeScript)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical

Illustrates configuring a Lexical state for non-primitive types like Dates. It shows how to implement custom parse, isEqual, and unparse functions to handle Date objects, ensuring proper serialization and comparison.

```typescript
const isoDateState = createState('isoDate', {
  parse: (v): null | Date => {
    const date = typeof v === 'string' ? new Date(v) : null;
    return date && !isNaN(date.valueOf()) ? date : null;
  },
  isEqual: (a, b) => a === b || (a && b && a.valueOf() === b.valueOf()),
  unparse: (v) => v && v.toString()
});

```

