### Create Effect for Signal Changes with Preact Signals

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_extension

Sets up a reactive effect that runs code in response to signal changes. The effect tracks accessed signals and re-executes the callback when they change. It can optionally return a cleanup function that runs before the next execution or when the effect is disposed.

```typescript
import { Signal, effect } from "@preact/signals-core";

const message = new Signal("Initial message");

const disposeEffect = effect(() => {
  console.log("Effect ran. Message:", message.value);
  // Optional cleanup function
  return () => {
    console.log("Effect cleanup.");
  };
});

message.value = "Updated message";
// Output: Effect ran. Message: Updated message

// To stop the effect:
disposeEffect();
// Output: Effect cleanup.
```

