### Create a Plain Signal (TypeScript)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_extension

Creates a reactive signal with a given initial value and optional configuration. Signals are fundamental to managing state reactively, allowing components or logic to automatically update when the signal's value changes. This function is part of the core signals library.

```typescript
import { signal, Signal } from "@preact/signals-core";

// Create a signal for a string
const textSignal: Signal<string> = signal("Initial Value");

// Create a signal for a number
const countSignal: Signal<number> = signal(0);

// Access the value
console.log(textSignal.value); // Output: "Initial Value"
console.log(countSignal.value); // Output: 0

// Update the value
textSignal.value = "Updated Value";
countSignal.value++;

console.log(textSignal.value); // Output: "Updated Value"
console.log(countSignal.value); // Output: 1
```

