### Basic Node ExportJSON Implementations for Versioning (TypeScript)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/concepts/serialization

This TypeScript code demonstrates basic `exportJSON` methods for a `TextNode` and an `ExtendedTextNode` subclass. It highlights how versioning can become problematic when a subclass overrides the superclass's version, leading to potential inconsistencies and lost version information.

```typescript
class TextNode {
  exportJSON() {
    return { /* ... */, version: 1 };
  }
}
class ExtendedTextNode extends TextNode {
  exportJSON() {
    return { ...super.exportJSON() };
  }
}

```

```typescript
class TextNode {
  exportJSON() {
    return { /* ... */, version: 2 };
  }
}
class ExtendedTextNode extends TextNode {
  exportJSON() {
    // The super's layout has changed, but the version information is lost
    return { ...super.exportJSON(), version: 1 };
  }
}

```

