### RootNode Methods: Cloning, Type Identification, and JSON Import

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical

This snippet focuses on methods related to node identity and serialization. `clone` creates a copy of the node. `getType` returns a unique string identifier for the node type. `importJSON` handles the deserialization of a node from its JSON representation, crucial for state persistence.

```typescript
/**
 * Clones this node, creating a new node with a different key and adding it to the EditorState (but not attaching it anywhere!). All nodes must implement this method.
 * @returns {RootNode}
 */
static clone(): RootNode;

/**
 * Returns the string type of this node. Every node must implement this and it MUST BE UNIQUE amongst nodes registered on the editor.
 * @returns {string}
 */
static getType(): string;

/**
 * Controls how the this node is deserialized from JSON. This is usually boilerplate, but provides an abstraction between the node implementation and serialized interface that can be important if you ever make breaking changes to a node schema (by adding or removing properties). See Serialization & Deserialization.
 * @param {SerializedRootNode} serializedNode
 * @returns {RootNode}
 */
static importJSON(serializedNode: SerializedRootNode): RootNode;
```

