### Synchronous Editor State Update with Discrete Option in Lexical

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/concepts/editor-state

Demonstrates how to force an immediate commit of editor state changes using the `discrete: true` option in `editor.update()`. This is crucial for scenarios like server-side state persistence where the update must be completed before subsequent operations, preventing the use of stale state.

```javascript
editor.update(() => {
  // manipulate the state...
}, {discrete: true});

saveToDatabase(editor.getEditorState().toJSON());
```

