### Convert Lexical Editor State to Markdown Server-Side (JavaScript)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/packages/lexical-headless

Shows how to convert Lexical editor state to Markdown format on a server using `@lexical/headless` and `@lexical/markdown`. This involves loading article state, setting it in a headless editor, and then converting it to Markdown.

```javascript
const { createHeadlessEditor } = require('@lexical/headless');
const { $convertToMarkdownString, TRANSFORMERS } = require('@lexical/markdown');

app.get('article/:id/markdown', async (req, res) => {
  const editor = createHeadlessEditor({
    nodes: [],
    onError: () => {},
  });

  const articleEditorStateJSON = await loadArticleBody(req.query.id);
  editor.setEditorState(editor.parseEditorState(articleEditorStateJSON));

  editor.update(() => {
    const markdown = $convertToMarkdownString(TRANSFORMERS);
    res.send(markdown);
  });
});
```

