### LexicalComposer Component (React)

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_react_LexicalComposer

The LexicalComposer component initializes and configures a Lexical editor instance within a React application. It requires an 'initialConfig' object to set up the editor's state, theme, and behavior. It returns a React Element that renders the editor.

```typescript
import { LexicalComposer } from '@lexical/react/LexicalComposer';
import { PlainTextMarkdownFormat } from '@lexical/react/PlainTextMarkdownFormat';

function Editor() {
  const initialConfig = {
    editorState: null,
    keyboardShortcuts: {
      // ...
    },
    namespace: 'MyEditor',
    nodes: [],
    onError: (error) => {
      console.error(error);
    },
    theme: {},
  };

  return (
    <LexicalComposer initialConfig={initialConfig}>
      {/* Child components that use the editor */}
      <PlainTextMarkdownFormat />
    </LexicalComposer>
  );
}
```

