Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_utils

The `mediaFileReader` function reads an array of `File` objects, validating them against a list of acceptable MIME types. It returns a promise that resolves to an array of objects, each containing file information and results. This function supports batched results and maintains the order of the files.

```typescript
mediaFileReader(files: File[], acceptableMimeTypes: string[]): Promise<object[]>
```

```javascript
const filesResult = await mediaFileReader(files, ['image/']);
filesResult.forEach(file => editor.dispatchCommand('INSERT_IMAGE', { src: file.result }));
```

