### LexicalNestedComposer Component API

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical_react_LexicalNestedComposer

Details about the LexicalNestedComposer component, its props, and how to use it.

```APIDOC
## LexicalNestedComposer Component

### Description
Provides a nested Lexical editor instance. This is useful for creating editors within specific nodes or complex editor structures. Note that the nested editor does not inherit plugins or registrations from the parent editor.

### Usage
```jsx
<LexicalNestedComposer initialEditor={nestedEditor} {...props}>
  {/* Child plugins and nodes */}
</LexicalNestedComposer>
```

### Props
#### `initialEditor` (LexicalEditor) - Required

The nested editor instance, typically created using `createEditor` with `parentEditor` set to the parent editor.

#### `children` (ReactNode) - Optional

Any children to be rendered within the nested editor, such as plugins or other React components. Plugins used by child nodes must also be instantiated here.

#### `initialTheme` (EditorThemeClasses) - Optional

An optional theme object to override the default theme for the nested editor.

#### `skipCollabChecks` (boolean) - Optional

If not explicitly set to `true`, rendering of children might be deferred until collaboration is ready when the collab plugin is active.

#### `skipEditableListener` (boolean) - Optional

If not explicitly set to `true`, the nested editor's editable state will automatically follow the parent editor's state. Setting it to `true` allows the nested editor to manage its own editable state independently. Available since v0.29.0.

#### `initialNodes` (readonly (KlassConstructor<typeof LexicalNode> | LexicalNodeReplacement)[]) - Optional (Deprecated)

This prop is deprecated and will be removed in v0.32.0. It is not safely or correctly implemented. Nodes should only be configured when creating the `initialEditor`.

### Example Usage for `initialEditor`
```javascript
import { createEditor } from 'lexical';
import { LexicalNestedComposer } from '@lexical/react/LexicalNestedComposer';
import { useLexicalComposerContext } from '@lexical/react/LexicalComposerContext';
import { useEffect } from 'react';

function MyNestedEditorNode() {
  const [editor] = useLexicalComposerContext();
  // Create a nested editor instance
  const nestedEditor = createEditor({ parentEditor: editor });

  useEffect(() => {
    // You can register plugins or set initial state on nestedEditor here
    // For example:
    // nestedEditor.registerCommand(MY_CUSTOM_COMMAND, () => {
    //   // handle command
    //   return true;
    // }, lexicalCommandPriority.LOW);
  }, [nestedEditor]);

  return (
    <LexicalNestedComposer initialEditor={nestedEditor}>
      {/* Add any plugins or nodes specific to this nested editor */}
    </LexicalNestedComposer>
  );
}
```

### Return Value

Returns a `Element` which renders the nested editor UI.
```

