### Node Information Methods

Source: https://lexical.dev/docs/api/modules/lexical

Methods for retrieving information about a node, such as its parents, siblings, text content, type, and top-level element.

```APIDOC
## Node Information Methods

### getParents()

**Description**: Returns a list of every ancestor of this node, all the way up to the RootNode.

**Method**: N/A (This is a method on a Node object, not an API endpoint)

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getPreviousSibling()

**Description**: Returns the "previous" sibling - that is, the node that comes before this one in the same parent.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getPreviousSiblings()

**Description**: Returns the "previous" siblings - that is, the nodes that come between this one and the first child of its parent, inclusive.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getTextContent()

**Description**: Returns the text content of the node. Override this for custom nodes that should have a representation in plain text format (for copy + paste, for example).

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getTextContentSize()

**Description**: Returns the length of the string produced by calling getTextContent on this node.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getTopLevelElement()

**Description**: Returns the highest (in the EditorState tree) non-root ancestor of this node, or null if none is found. See $isRootOrShadowRoot for more information on which Elements comprise "roots".

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getTopLevelElementOrThrow()

**Description**: Returns the highest (in the EditorState tree) non-root ancestor of this node, or throws if none is found. See $isRootOrShadowRoot for more information on which Elements comprise "roots".

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getType()

**Description**: Returns the string type of this node.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### getWritable()

**Description**: Returns a mutable version of the node using $cloneWithProperties if necessary. Will throw an error if called outside of a Lexical Editor LexicalEditor.update callback.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A

### is()

**Description**: Returns true if the provided node is the exact same one as this node, from Lexical's perspective. Always use this instead of referential equality.

**Method**: N/A

**Endpoint**: N/A
```

